<item>
            <title>[SPARK-7718] Speed up data source partitioning by avoiding cleaning closures</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7718</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new partitioning support strategy creates a bunch of RDDs (1 per partition, could be up to several thousands), then calls `mapPartitions` on every single one of these RDDs. This causes us to clean the same closure many times. Since we provide the closure in Spark we know for sure it is serializable, so we can bypass the cleaning for performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yhuai&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yhuai&quot;&gt;yhuai&lt;/a&gt; cleaning 5000 closures take up to 6-7 seconds in a 12 seconds job that involves data source partitioning.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
